    <text id="F0646T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Hover tells his mother about his marching orders and about how he has to carry
                    eight days of rations. He also mentions a portrait of himself and says that he
                    is sending money home.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Mother</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1863-04-20">April the 20 1863 </date>
                        <name type="place">Camp near Bell Plane landing <orig reg="Virginia">verginia</orig></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Mother </salute>
                </opener>

                <p>i take my pen in hand to inform you that i am well at this present time and hope
                    that <orig reg="these">those</orig> few lines will find you all in the same
                    state of good <orig reg="health">helth</orig>. We <orig reg="are">ar</orig> in
                    our old camp yet But i dont <orig reg="know">no</orig> how long we will stay
                        <orig reg="here">heur</orig> for we are under marching orders now and <orig
                        reg="can't">cant</orig> tell <orig reg="what">wat</orig> day we will <orig
                        reg="have">haf</orig> to march we had <orig reg="very">verrey</orig>
                    <orig reg="nice">nise</orig> weather <orig reg="here">heur</orig> for the last
                    few days and when we do march we <orig reg="have">hav</orig> eight days <unclear>
                        <orig reg="rations">rashings</orig>
                    </unclear> to convoy on our backs We will <orig reg="have">hav</orig> about
                        <orig reg="forty">fortey</orig> five or <orig reg="fifty">fiftey</orig>
                    pounds to convey on our backs You wanted my likeness and i had a <orig
                        reg="chance">caince</orig> to get it taken the other day and i got it taken
                    and now i send it to you and ten <orig reg="dollars">dolers</orig> with it and i
                    want you to send Me twenty five <orig reg="cents">sents</orig> worth of post
                    stamps if you <orig reg="can">cin</orig> get them you <orig reg="can">cin</orig>
                    <orig reg="use">yous</orig> the ten <orig reg="dollars">dolers</orig> if you
                    want to I must bring my letter to a close for the present time. nothing more at
                    present time. But <orig reg="write">rite</orig> soon and let me <orig reg="know"
                        >no</orig> whether you got the likeness and money or not.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute> </salute>
                    <signed>Augustus Hover </signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">
                        <name type="recipient">to His Mother </name>
                    </seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
